description:
When I was a young boy (1950's), I learned to play golf by closely watching the best players at the course I grew up on. I would then stand in front of a window and copy their swings... then I would go to the practice area to ingrain that look and new feeling to muscle memory. That WAS and STILL IS a great way to learn! It's called SELF-DISCOVERY! 

When you discover a helpful motion or thought ALL BY YOURSELF, YOU WILL NEVER FORGET IT! - I never have!  

At the age of 78, I'm still a mid single-digit player. My goal with this YouTube channel is to provide a platform for TEACHING and LEARNING! I will provide videos and detailed descriptions of the finest golfers in the world, their swings and some of their finest shots so YOU can learn and improve as I have. 

The focus here is geared toward TEACHING and LEARNING the short game (putting, chipping, pitching and wedge play from 120-yards in), but you will also see some of the finest, Tour-Proven full swings and descriptions as well.⛳️

description:
No, I am not dead. I merely wish to not be redundant. Will only upload when I get a video of something that isn't already on my channel. Also please note that the majority of these videos I made when I was a kid / early teenager, and am now a Junior Biology Major, and I know better than to do some of the stupid stuff I did. description:
Mike Orazzi is a New England photographer and newspaper photojournalist based in Connecticut. He owns too many Jeeps and chainsaws, like mud, working outside and of course photography. The photography pays the bills. 
I use Nikon photography gear active cameras that I use are from the Nikon Z9, Nikon D850, Nikon D500, Nikon D3, I still sometimes use a D7100 or A D300.
For glass I have a 400f2.8, 300 f2.8, 200-400 f4, 70-200f2.8, wide glass doesn't get used much.
For videos I have been having a lot of fun with a Canon Vixia HF G70. 

Everything else you see here spends all of my money and then some. Check here for random videos of tractors, Jeeps, something diesel, news, and whatever else we happen to be doing. #compacttractor #photographer #photography #nikonz9 #z9 #outdoors #canon  Use the playlists to easier navigation. 
See more work at: http://mikeorazzi.smugmug.com/

description:
Slow Motion videos of nature, explosions, and more can be found on the first slow motion channel on YouTube! .

From silly to science, Emmy Award winner Alan Teitel and his UltraSlo Studio create compelling slow motion video images for online entertainment and education. Slow motion videos from the Ultraslo stock video library are used in documentaries commercials and scientific research world wide. Slow motion videos from UltraSlo have been viewed oner a quarter of a billion times on all the sites that love to stream  slow motion videos around the world

Alan has a unique outlook and viewing perspective based on his twenty-five years of slow motion and 3d work which allow him to see the world at a much different speed. Alan is a director, cinematographer and producer of national commercials, documentaries, and dramatic scenes. 

Alan won two Emmy's for Cinematography and Technical Achievement. Alan has been nominated six times for his outstanding work on broadcast television

description:
Fourguysguns.com is a place for anyone from new shooters, to those curious about guns, to get help on anything from gun disassembly, cleaning, holding and aiming to proper range safety and etiquette. We didnʼt grow up hunting, only one of us was in the military and in all honesty... we all learned the hard way what to do and what NOT to do with all these things.

So here we are. FourGuysGuns.com - More than a snazzy logo. We have video, we have stills, we have some of the most popular "First -Time" guns for pistol, rifle, shotgun. We have taken them apart, put them back together, we have broken pins, shot springs across the room and jerk the pistol down and left (trust me, itʼs easier if you just cut your pinky off entirely) and made all the mistakes most Noobs make, and we are here to share them with you, so you donʼt have to. And hell, maybe have some ball breaking fun along the way.

description:
MIKROTRON - a brand of SVS-Vistek GmbH

The MIKROTRON brand is internationally known in the machine vision market for small, particularly robust High-Speed cameras that are used in industrial and scientific applications as well as in sports, advertising and nature filming.

SVS-Vistek GmbH has exceptional know-how in industrial image processing as an innovative manufacturer of high-quality industrial CCD and CMOS cameras for more than 35 years. 
We develop and produce a wide range of standard cameras as well as cameras with the highest resolutions and highest speeds, above-average image quality and all relevant interfaces in our own clean rooms at our headquarters in Gilching near Munich: Quality Made in Germany! 
With subsidiaries in the USA and Japan as well as a large partner network, we can advise, support and serve customers of many markets worldwide.

description: Deux nomades sur une moto/dragon de la chance✌️ Suivez notre voyage sans fin sur le dos de Falkor notre BMW GS800 🐲🏍️ Nathalia et Vincent, ensemble depuis 2002, on explore le monde de différentes manières : à pieds, en tandem, en voilier, à moto, etc. On partage avec humour, légèreté et effets spéciaux totalement foireux, nos aventures sur cette belle planète. Depuis le 01.08.2021, nous sommes à nouveau sur les routes du monde pour une belle histoire sans fin. Après avoir fait tourner une bouteille de pinard sur une carte, nous voilà parti pour un voyage sans destination, ni durée. Le but: rencontrer des personnes/organisations inspirantes, qui vivent en symbiose avec notre planète. Réaliser des bénévolats et échanges de services en offrant de nos compétences ou de notre temps pour des projets qui nous parlent. Nous voyageons sur Falkor (le dragon porteur de chance), notre moto BMW GS 800. Quand rien n'est prévu, tout est possible. Retrouvez-nous sur Instagram & Polarsteps.

description:
The Splash Lab seeks to unravel the physical mechanisms of fluid behaviors, through a novel 3D volumetric measurement method known as Synthetic Aperture Imaging and imbedded instrumentation (e.g., accelerometers, etc). We experimentally analyze fluid systems such as fluid-structure interactions, multi-phase flows, and free surface phenomena.  Currently, we are funded by the Office of Naval Research and the National Science Foundation to improve our imaging techniques and elucidate topics from skipping balls to projectile water entry.  Most of our projects are fun and interesting as we try to make them accessible to the public through high quality photography and video production!
For more information
Website: http://splashlab.byu.edu
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/byusplashlab
Twitter: https://twitter.com/BYUSplashLab
Instagram: BYUSplashLab

"SimonKr" was founded in 2005 by Simon Krzic and is currently one of the leading stock footage production companies in the industry. The main focus is to refine and perfect our proven approach to the production of high-quality stock footage. Early on, we submitted stills and footage to most of the major microstock websites, but in June 2007 exclusivity was signed with iStockvideo for the RF footage program and were soon invited to contribute to Getty Images as well.

The folks at iStock refer to us as "the most prolific videographer on the planet". With more than 20.000 active video files in our iStock portfolio, our work is likely to appear in almost any content search initiated at iStock. 

Our portfolio includes themes from everyday lifestyle, business concepts, wildlife, world-wide travel footage and mostly human emotions. You can check our portfolio here: http://www.simonkr.com/portfolio

description: A selection of animated shorts, videos and documentary productions exploring the arts through a contemporary Jewish lens. Most of these productions were created by students at a pluralistic Jewish high school in Los Angeles that was affectionately dubbed “NewJew" by its early students.
